8:
I thought the Guild was supposed to 
handing out quests, not chores.
12:
All important tasks, Alk. 
The first step to any journey is seeing 
that your own house is in order.
18: Clyde. What do you think of this shiner?
22:
Would it kill you to respond with more 
than a syllable? 
Ugh, you never show an interest in any 
of my wares!
24:
Why do you even keep coming?
...Y-you wouldn't be hoping to take ME 
out, by any—
30:
...Welcoming to customers. 
The mark of a good shop.
35:
Yeah, the merchant seems really 
friendly. 
Think she'll be willing to help us out.
40:
Um, excuse me? The Guild sent us here 
to make some purchases, and—
43: The Guild?! Ooh, sounds like gold to me!
45:
We're looking for twenty sets of 
beginner equipment.
50:
If that's the case, why don't you help 
yourself to some of these swords?
56:
Why? I'm running a shop here! 
You can't monopolize my goods!
...But, uh, if you wanted to monopolize 
ME, on the other hand—
80:
I won't rest... until all cursed weapons 
have turned to dust!
98: Not just any weapons! My WARES!
106:
Recompensation. But it's probably only 
worth half of what you had.
108:
You knew all along then... 
that my goods were jinxed.
110:
I have a history with cursed weapons... 
I'm trying to erase them from my future.
112:
Next time, sell swords that aren't 
possessed. It'll be better for business.
121:
Wow. He was cool. One of those 
hardcore soldier types.
137: I am no rabbit. I was once human.
140: You and I... We are both cursed.
146: That wasn't me! It was the shield.
150: Then is the shield what cursed you?
157:
It came from the Kaleidoscope. 
Merchant said it had a mind of its own, 
capable of analyzing the flow of battle.
159:
It's also supposed to answer my 
questions every time I say "Hey, Shield," 
but...
168:
...It talks when it wants to. 
I can't take it off. So most people think 
I'm... rude.
172:
Clyde. If you have nowhere else to go, 
join us.
177:
Yes. I am also cursed. 
We may be able to help each other.
181:
I'd appreciate that. 
I just ran out of funds.
185:
Wait... Did you give the shopkeep ALL 
your money?
